OL,3,CJersey's minimum wage set to rise to
OL,4,C#13 per hour
OL,6,FThe minimum wage in Jersey is set to
OL,7,Fincrease to #13 per hour from April
OL,8,F2025.
OL,10,FThere will be changes to the island's
OL,11,Femployment law, as well as a package
OL,12,Fput in place to help employers and
OL,13,Femployees adjust to the changes.
OL,15,FThe Minister for Social Security,
OL,16,FDeputy Lyndsay Feltham, is updating
OL,17,Fthe minimum wage from 1 April 2025 in
OL,18,Fpreparation for April 2026, when the
OL,19,Fminimum wage will be set as two thirds
OL,20,Fof the 2024 median wage.
