OL,3,CJersey's minimum wage set to rise to
OL,4,C#13 per hour
OL,6,FDeputy Feltham said: "The transition
OL,7,Fto a living wage is an important
OL,8,Fpriority of this Government as it
OL,9,Fdirectly supports many in our
OL,10,Fcommunity who are most likely to be
OL,11,Fstruggling with the cost of living.
OL,13,F"We are staging the transition over
OL,14,Ftwo years, and providing some
OL,15,Ftemporary support measures to
OL,16,Femployees during that time."
